<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={6.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={13.98}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={13.71}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={6.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={13.98}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={13.71}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>25</li><li>80.02</li><li>74.68</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}^{{2}}={13.98}^{{2}}+{13.71}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({13.98}\right)}{\left({13.71}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{36}={195.4404}+{187.9641}-{383.3316}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{347.4045}=-{383.3316}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.9062767066425}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={25.00421334131}={25}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({25.00421334131}\right)}}}}{{6.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{13.98}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.29864614680195}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{0.29864614680195}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={80.01587708242}\approx{80.02}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25.00421334131}+{80.01587708242}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={74.676925080614}\approx{74.68}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

